title: Grateful Dead Live at Hill Auditorium on 1971-12-14
description:
Set 1

Truckin', Sugaree, Mr. Charlie, Beat It On Down The Line, Loser, Jack Straw, Next Time You See Me, Tennessee Jed, El Paso, Big Railroad Blues, Me & My Uncle, Run Rudolph Run, Black Peter, Playin' In The Band, Casey Jones

Set 2

Ramble On Rose, Mexicali Blues, Big Boss Man, Cryptical Envelopement-> Drums-> The Other One-> Me & My Uncle Jam-> The Other One-> Wharf Rat, Sugar Magnolia, You Win Again, Not Fade Away-> Goin' Down The Road Feelin' Bad-> Not Fade Away

"Stars & Stripes Forever" tuning before 'You Will Again' - Other artist(s): NRPS

reviews.review_text:
Other One > Wharf Rat symphonic. worth the price of admission alone.
lots of other goodies throughout.

thanks to all involved !
- This string at the end of '71 is proving consistently epic.
12-14-71' Ann Arbor This is a very well played show from the end of 1971.Pig is in fine form and the addition of Ron brings  a nice new complexity to their sound.Really not to be missed.

Happy 50th! boys are on fire... 50 years ago today. Yeeeeewwwwww!!! 

Many thanks to Charlie Miller and his endless efforts!!!!!!!!!!
